title: For Sale/Trade:  FS/FT:  H&A Hopkins & Allen #6 Double Action, Non-working
postcontent: Here's a package deal for you tinkerers and repairmen;   This is a 1800's Hopkins & Allen .32 Long revolver,   in relatively good exterior condition, and certainly a C&R.   The barrel and cylinders look pretty worn but the rifling is still visible.  It comes with a bag of about 100 loose rounds that appear to be ancient,   and a partial box of about 40 rounds that are probably from the 70's  It also comes with an Ideal mold and primer seating tool in .32   Before I broke it,  I put a few rounds through it,  without any issues,   it's inaccurate as hell, and has less recoil that a .22 LR.  I then took it apart and cleaned all the rust and crap out of the interior, and busted a pin retainer while re-assembling it.    If you are familiar with these, the main spring is held in place under the back strap by a single pin,  and that pin is anchored to the backstrap by two paper thin castings on the frame.   I broke one of those off and now there's no good way to anchor the mainspring in place.    SO -   If you're good with silver soldering or brazing you should be able to attach a new flange,   otherwise it's just a really cool paperweight.       These go for about $60 in parts on Ebay, but frankly I just don't want to mess with selling individual parts, so I'm making a package deal and setting a realistic price that will sell.  $50 Cash or trade for the equivalent in ammo,     make me an offer folks.

The CZ 75 SP-01 is the first full size handgun (4.61” bbl) from CZ to feature the improved manufacturing technology and ergonomics of the NATO-approved CZ 75 Compact P-01 model. Borrowing from the improved grip geometry of the compact P-01, the SP-01 utilizes an extended beavertail to protect shooter’s strong hand as well as allowing for a deeper and more secure grip. The new grip geometry, checkering in key areas on the front and back straps, and redistribution of mass provided by the accessory rail noticeably decrease the perceived recoil from previous models and allows for more rapid target acquisition and transition.

The SP-01 was designed as a military and law enforcement duty sidearm. The new model is currently in use by security forces fighting the war on terrorism. Thanks to its exceptional accuracy and superior handling characteristics, the CZ 75 SP-01 has also found supporters in the field of sport and target shooting. title: For Sale:  Sig Sauer SAS Custom Shop P238 .380 Pistol
postcontent:
The P238 SAS has gone through a radical dehorning process resulting in an ultra smooth, snag free profile that’s ideal for concealed carry. It’s just a fraction of the size of full-size pistols. A smart looking, small handgun built with the same accuracy and reliability as large frame SIG SAUER pistols. With an overall length of just 5.5 inches a height of 3.96 inches, and weighing just 15.2 ounces, the SIG SAUER P238 is the ultimate firepower in an all metal frame concealed pistol. The P238 SAS is built on an anodized alloy beavertail style frame with rosewood grips for comfort and a secure hold during rapid-fire usage. The stainless steel slide features the popular trademarked SIG SAUER slide serrations, corrosion resistant Nitron finish and SIGLITE® Night Sights. The SIG SAUER P238 SAS is has a lockable hard case, one kydex holster and one 6 round magazine. The SIG Sauer P238 is a compact .380 ACP caliber, single-action pistol. It is a version of the Colt Mustang pistol with a classic SIG Sauer scalloped slide and finger relief under the trigger guard. Grip panels are fluted polymer making this an all-metal frame firearm in competition with plastic-framed pistols in the same class like the Ruger LCP, S&W Bodyguard and the Kel-Tec P-3. 

This one while used, has been used very lightly. The lady who brought it in to me, brought the ammo with it and there were 24 missing. She said that was all that had ever been shot through it. I am in NKY, and will take cash in NKY if you want this beauty.
